---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../../styles/page-main.css';
---

<Layout
	title="References"
	description="Developer references: links and files recommended on kspice.dev."
>
	<main class="main">
		<h1>References</h1>
		<p class="lede">Links and files I use or recommend for day-to-day development.</p>
		<section class="section" aria-labelledby="refs-list-heading">
			<h2 id="refs-list-heading">Curated links</h2>
			<ul class="cards">
				<li>
					<a
						class="card"
						href="https://barrgroup.com/sites/default/files/barr_c_coding_standard_2018.pdf"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>
						<h3>Barr C coding standard (2018)</h3>
						<p>
							The Barr Group’s embedded C coding standard as a PDF. The baseline that the
							<span class="inline-code">.clang-format</span> entry below is meant to approximate.
						</p>
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a
						class="card"
						href="https://github.com/petertorelli/clang-format-barr-c/blob/master/.clang-format"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>
						<h3>Barr C <span class="inline-code">.clang-format</span></h3>
						<p>
							Peter Torelli’s <span class="inline-code">.clang-format</span> that approximates the Barr
							Group’s embedded C coding guidelines (2018) via clang-format. Useful for consistent C
							code styling.
						</p>
					</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
